      • logDelay

        public <T> T logDelay(String subject,
                      Supplier<T> action)
        Performs the given action and logs how long it took to complete.
        Type Parameters:
        T - The return type of the given action.
        Parameters:
        subject - Short action description used when logging just before the action is started and immediatly after the action completes.
        action - The action to be executed.
        Returns:
        The same value returned by the given action.
